ACCDM proposes:

> Dark matter behaves as effectively standard cold dark matter in the early universe but develops emergent adaptive structure inside mature rotating galaxies.



The framework does NOT replace ΛCDM cosmology.

Instead, it modifies the microscopic nature of dark matter particles.


