15. Key Next Step

The most important next step is observational testing.

Specifically:

> Determine whether unexplained galaxy rotation support correlates with ordered magnetic-field geometry and coherent galactic flow structure across large galaxy samples.



If such correlations appear robustly beyond standard ΛCDM expectations, ACCDM may represent evidence for previously unknown emergent dark-sector dynamics.

If no correlation exists, the framework would likely fail.


---

Conclusion

ACCDM proposes that dark matter is not a simple collisionless particle gas, but a composite adaptive hidden-sector medium capable of emergent organisation inside mature galaxies.

The framework preserves the large-scale successes of ΛCDM while introducing new galaxy-scale physics that may explain:

flat rotation curves,

baryon-dark matter coupling,

and galactic structural diversity.


Its scientific value depends entirely on whether its predicted galaxy-scale correlations survive observational testing and simulation.
